cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.DC. 

The paper deals with geometric spanners, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for constructing the spanner, as well as probabilistic analysis (cs.DM) of the expected time complexity. The use of the well-separated pair decomposition (WSPD) and local information suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) component. Finally, the paper presents a new algorithm for a well-studied problem, which could fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) if the algorithm is parallelizable.
